<h3 class=3D"home2" style=3D"text-align:left;color:#F57E08">Distance calcul=
ator</h3>
<p class=3D"home2">Travelmath provides an online travel distance calculator=
 to help you
measure both flying distances and driving distances.
You can then compare the two results to see the difference.
<a href=3D"https://www.travelmath.com/distance/"><strong>Flight distance</s=
trong></a>
is computed from a GPS-accurate great circle formula, which
gives you the straight line distance "as the crow flies".
<a href=3D"https://www.travelmath.com/drive-distance/"><strong>Driving dist=
ance</strong></a>
by car is determined from the actual turn-by-turn driving
directions. If you want to split the distance
with a friend, you can use the <a href=3D"https://www.travelmath.com/halfwa=
y/"><strong>halfway point</strong></a>
calculator to find the best place to meet.
For a long distance trip, you can <a href=3D"https://www.travelmath.com/sto=
pping-points/"><strong>plan a road trip with stops</strong></a>.
Or browse the
<a href=3D"https://mileagemath.com/"><strong>mileage charts</strong></a>
for any state or country.</p>

